{"title_page": "Richard Barlas", "text_new": "{{short description|British civil servant}}\n'''Sir Richard Douglas Barlas''' {{post-nominals|KCB|OBE}} (1916 - 1982) was a British [[civil servant]] who served as a clerk in the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]].\n\nBarlas was commissioned as a [[pilot officer]] in the [[Royal Air Force Volunteer Reserve]] on 7 December 1937,<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=34461|date=7 December 1937|page=7662 |supp= }}</ref> but relinquished his commission on the grounds of ill-health on 30 November 1938.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=34588|date=10 January 1939|page=220 |supp= }}</ref> He rejoined the RAF during the [[Second World War]] and was promoted to [[war substantive]] [[flying officer]] on 28 December 1940.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=35083|date=21 February 1941|page=1085 |supp= }}</ref> He was made an Officer of the [[Order of the British Empire]] on 1 January 1944 while holding the rank of [[wing commander (rank)|Wing Commander]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=36309|date=1 January 1944|page=17 |supp=y }}</ref>\n\nBarlas was appointed a Companion of the [[Order of the Bath]] while serving as Second Clerk Assistant and Clerk of Committees in the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=44600|date=8 June 1963|page=6301 |supp=y }}</ref> He served as [[Clerk of the House of Commons]] between 1976 and 1979, and was appointed Knight Commander of the Order of the Bath in the [[1977 Silver Jubilee and Birthday Honours]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=47234|date=11 June 1977|page=7082 |supp=y }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Barlas, Richard}}\n[[Category:1916 births]]\n[[Category:1982 deaths]]\n[[Category:British civil servants]]\n[[Category:Clerks of the House of Commons]]\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of the Bath]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Royal Air Force officers]]\n[[Category:Royal Air Force Volunteer Reserve personnel of World War II]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British civil servant}}\n'''Sir Richard Douglas Barlas''' {{post-nominals|KCB|OBE}} (1916 - 1982) was a British [[civil servant]] who served as a clerk in the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]].\n\nBarlas was commissioned as a [[pilot officer]] in the [[Royal Air Force Volunteer Reserve]] on 7 December 1937,<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=34461|date=7 December 1937|page=7662 |supp= }}</ref> but relinquished his commission on the grounds of ill-health on 30 November 1938.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=34588|date=10 January 1939|page=220 |supp= }}</ref> He rejoined the RAF during the [[Second World War]] and was promoted to [[war substantive]] [[flying officer]] on 28 December 1940.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=35083|date=21 February 1941|page=1085 |supp= }}</ref> He was made an Officer of the [[Order of the British Empire]] on 1 January 1944 while holding the rank of [[wing commander]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=36309|date=1 January 1944|page=17 |supp=y }}</ref>\n\nBarlas was appointed a Companion of the [[Order of the Bath]] while serving as Second Clerk Assistant and Clerk of Committees in the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=44600|date=8 June 1963|page=6301 |supp=y }}</ref> He served as [[Clerk of the House of Commons]] between 1976 and 1979, and was appointed Knight Commander of the Order of the Bath in the [[1977 Silver Jubilee and Birthday Honours]].<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=47234|date=11 June 1977|page=7082 |supp=y }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Barlas, Richard}}\n[[Category:1916 births]]\n[[Category:1982 deaths]]\n[[Category:British civil servants]]\n[[Category:Clerks of the House of Commons]]\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of the Bath]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Royal Air Force officers]]\n[[Category:Royal Air Force Volunteer Reserve personnel of World War II]]\n", "name